To slice it all another way, Perl is just a lovely little tool for all
kinds of things, including dictionary lookups.  Just love a language with
associative arrays (hash tables) as a basic data type!  Here are the
different decryptions of the ciphertext, sorted by the number of 3-letter
/usr/dict/words or better in the plaintext, for 6 words or better:

	WDS   IC  Key      Plaintext
